<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Paper: Army Officer Files Complaint  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Army's most senior female officer has
accused a fellow general of sexual harassment, The Washington Times
reported today.
</P>
<P>
   The newspaper reported that Lt. Gen. Claudia Kennedy, the Army's
deputy chief of staff for intelligence, filed a complaint stemming
from an incident in her Pentagon office in 1996. The Times quoted
an unidentified Army source as saying Kennedy accused the fellow
general of ''inappropriate touching.''
</P>
<P>
   The Army today refused to comment on the Times report. Col.
Edwin Veiga, an Army spokesman, said that as a matter of standard
practice, ''We're not going to verify whether there's an ongoing
investigation or not.''
</P>
<P>
   Veiga said Kennedy, when informed of the Times article, said she
would not comment.
</P>
<P>
   The newspaper report did not say when Kennedy filed her
complaint, nor did it identify the accused general.
</P>
<P>
   The Times said the Defense Department inspector general's office
is investigating the accusation and has interviewed people who were
on Kennedy's staff in 1996 when she was a major general and held
the position of assistant deputy chief for intelligence.
</P>
<P>
   Susan Hansen, a Pentagon spokeswoman, said the Defense
Department inspector general's office is not investigating the
matter. It is possible that the Army's own inspector general is
handling the matter, but the Army would not confirm that.
</P>
<P>
   The Times said a former officer told its reporter that he was
interviewed by the accused general's defense lawyer, who asked him
about Kennedy's ''demeanor on a certain October date in 1996 and
about her office layout.''
</P>
<P>
   The Times said it could not learn the identity of the accused
general. The newspaper said an Army lawyer it believed to be
representing the accused general declined to comment to its
reporter.
</P>
<P>
   Kennedy, 52, is not married. She recently told her staff that
she plans to retire this summer.
</P>
</TEXT>
