<HEADLINE> Five Die in Ohio House Fire  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LIMA, Ohio (AP) -- A 33-year-old woman and four teen-agers died
when they were trapped inside a burning two-story house.
</P>
<P>
   Rodney Bunley, the woman's 41-year-old fiance, escaped the blaze
Wednesday night by jumping from an upstairs window, fire Chief Bob
Brinkman said today. He was hospitalized in good condition.
</P>
<P>
   Marian Wright, 33; her children Marshonda, 13, and Marquis, 16;
and Bunley's children Rodnina Bunley, 17, and Ravis Bunley, 14,
were killed.
</P>
<P>
   Fire Chief John Brookman said investigators believe the fire
started on the house's first floor, probably on the front porch.
</P>
<P>
   Erin O'Brien, who lives next door, said she heard Bunley playing
and laughing with the children less than half an hour before
hearing an explosion.
</P>
<P>
   ''We heard this loud crash and then somebody started
screaming,'' O'Brien said. ''It happened so quick and so fast we
couldn't even get the car out of the driveway.''
</P>
