<HEADLINE> Parton To Be Host of Country Awards  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Dolly Parton will be the host of the
Academy of Country Music Awards show.
</P>
<P>
   The May 3 ceremony in Universal City, Calif., to be broadcast
live on CBS, has not used a host the past two years. Producers said
Thursday the no-host format allowed for more performances by
country stars.
</P>
<P>
   ''Very few people have the ability to host this kind of show,''
said ACM Awards spokesman Paul Shefrin. ''There are very few Billy
Crystals in the world. When we found out Dolly might want to do it,
we decided to make the change.''
</P>
<P>
   The nominees for the top award of best entertainer are Tim
McGraw; his wife, Faith Hill; the Dixie Chicks; Sawyer Brown and
Shania Twain.
</P>
