<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Gain in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo's main share index gained slightly early
Friday after an overnight decline on Wall Street. The U.S. dollar
was higher against the yen.
</P>
<P>
   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average gained 9.53 points,
or 0.05 percent, to 20,451.03 in the first 30 minutes of trading.
On Thursday, the average closed down 265.15 points, or 1.28
percent.
</P>
<P>
   The dollar bought 105.84 yen, up 0.30 yen from late Thursday in
Tokyo and also above its late New York level of 105.46 yen
overnight.
</P>
<P>
   On the stock market, the Nikkei started lower after overnight
falls in U.S. high technology issues, but managed to move into
positive territory on buying of domestic demand-related shares.
</P>
<P>
   But traders said the Tokyo market remained weak overall on
profit-taking by corporate investors at the fiscal year-end and
drops on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
   In New York, the Dow Jones industrial average fell 38.47 to
10,916.25 at Thursday's finish. The Nasdaq composite index closed
at 4,457.89, down 186.78, or 4.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the
first section was down 8.40 points, or 0.49 percent, to 1,704.05.
The TOPIX finished down 20.39 points, or 1.18 percent, the previous
day.
</P>
<P>
   In currency dealings, the dollar followed through on its
overnight strength in New York and was also boosted on a Japanese
government report showing continued weakness in Japan's economy.
</P>
<P>
   The government said that the Tokyo-area consumer price index
fell 0.7 percent in March from a year earlier for the eighth
monthly year-on-year decline.
</P>
<P>
   Japan is struggling to bail out of its worst economic downturn
in 50 years.
</P>
<P>
   In other currencies, the euro was traded at 101.75 yen, up from
100.47 yen late Thursday in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
   The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond rose
to 1.8000 percent from Thursday's finish of 1.7900 percent. Its
price fell 0.09 point to 100.85.
(km-dj)
</P>
</TEXT>
