<HEADLINE> Two people killed in crash at Saratoga County airport  </HEADLINE>
AP Photo
<TEXT>
<P>
   MILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- A flight instructor and student were killed
when a single-engine airplane crashed and caught fire shortly after
takeoff from Saratoga County airport Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   A nearby resident saw the four-seater Cessna fixed wing aircraft
turn upside down and fall along the edge of a densely wooded area
in the southwest corner of the airport at around 2:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   The deceased are 24-year-old Daniel T. Melita of Gloversville,
the instructor; and 31-year-old Alfred W. Sutch Jr. of Broadalbin,
according to the E.M. Rooney, a chief deputy with the Saratoga
County sheriff's office. Officials did not say who was flying the
plane.
</P>
<P>
   The bodies were removed by late afternoon and autopsies were
planned.
</P>
<P>
   National Transportation Safety Board officials from New Jersey
were en route to the scene Thursday night.
</P>
