<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-30 23:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blackhawks 4, Maple Leafs 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Jocelyn Thibault made 27 saves for his third
shutout of the season as the Chicago Blackhawks beat Toronto 4-0 on
Thursday to end a three-game winless streak.
</P>
<P>
   Alex Zhamnov and Michael Nylander each had a goal and assist for
Chicago, which ended Toronto's two-game winning streak. Anders
Eriksson and Bob Probert also scored for the Blackhawks.
</P>
<P>
   The Maple Leafs are 3-5-0 since March 15, with four of the five
losses to teams out of playoff contention.
</P>
<P>
   Eriksson opened the scoring with 1:24 left in the first period,
beating screened goalie Glenn Healy with a 50-foot shot.
</P>
<P>
   After Zhamnov was high-sticked by Dmitri Yushkevich, the Chicago
forward scored during the ensuing power play to make it 2-0 lead at
5:51 of the second period.
</P>
<P>
   One of Thibault's best stops came with 2:50 left in the second,
when he made a point-blank pad save on Mats Sundin.
</P>
<P>
   Nylander made it 3-0 at 1:36 of the third period on a 25-foot
wrist shot that went under Healy's blocker. Probert scored at 5:53,
deflecting in Steve Sullivan's shot from a sharp angle.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
